# PvtPpr-Generator
Pass inputs through nodejs to generate a paper type result for the user to publish their thoughts without needing more than their browser. Uses itty.bitty.site and the nodejs encoding for the output results. This generator can also run off itty.bitty.site technology for fully offline encoding, decoding & reading.</br>
</br>

## What Does PvtPpr Do?
PvtPpr allows anyone with a browser to build paper-type documents to store thoughts and documents online without servers. Users of PvtPpr can now place ads in their papers as well as monetize with <a href="https://bittube.app" target="_blank">Bittube Airtime</a>.

## PvtPpr Examples
There is a dedicated PvtPpr Newschain that helps explain different possible features of PvtPpr. This newschain is the official by one of the 3Jokers and is found at the short link, <a href="https://3dd.in/pvtppr" target="_blank">3dd.in/pvtppr</a>. This is the longest known Newschain that goes back to the very first PvtPpr, the example.<ol>3Gxd's Newchain: <a href="https://rebrand.ly/3GxdPvtPpr" target="_blank">3GxD's PvtPpr</a></ol><ol>3D's Crypto & Tech Newchain: <a href="https://3dd.in/3d-pov" target="_blank">3D's C&T Pov</a></ol></br>To get your Newschain located here, place the request for change.

## What's a Newschain?
A newschain is the blockchain type chain based on hashlinks and shortlinked-hashlinks. Block size isn't hard-coded but deiced by the code. Each Newschain is a block in a personal pvtppr blockchain. The newschain is self building by the author. The author chooses which chain they attach their paper to which builds the newschain but eventually (if full hashlinks are being used to build the chain) the PvtPpr Generator will not generate the next PvtPpr. When this occurs the block is full and the code will not encode to the hashlink. This happens becuase of the length of the hashlink being produced by the new encoding. If the hashlink is too long (approximately over 500,000 characters) the encoding will not encode the next paper so a new block will be needed.

## Newschain Blocks
Neschain Blocks that are full must be stored seperatly from the newschain. These blocks can be stored offline (by paper), online (cloud storage/personal server/pastebin/IPFS) or personal stroage (offline digital storage i.e.: harddrive, sdd, on a computer). Blocks cannot be used as a "previous page" link in the PvtPpr Generator but the storage link of the block can be.

It is possible to build a singe PvtPpr page that is it's own block, this means that there is so much information that the finial result cannot be stroed via shortlinks (approximately over 200,000 characters).

## Why Shortlinks?
Shortlinks are the unsafe way to store PvtPprs becuase it reduces the length of the link allowing quantum and supercomputers to be able to guess the links much faster. The only good shortlinks gives is for public PvtPprs, where the papers are intended to be read by the public like a blog, website or forum. Using TinyURL we can hide our PvtPprs in plainsight with the company of thousands of other shortlinks, a.k.a. <i><b>hiding in the crowd</b></i>.

## PvtPpr Doesn't Distribute
PvtPpr doesn't distribute your papers. Since the papers are generated on the user's machine/device, there's no way to know that a paper exists without sharing it to others. This is why PvtPpr doesn't ditribute, so the user can opt-in to distribution of their paper/newschain.

## IPFS
Inter Planetary File System allows anyone to have a form of server. IPFS can be used within hashnets and meshnets which is what PvtPpr Newschains are (Hash based Meshnets). IPFS can be used to store PvtPpr Blocks as well as entrie Newschains.

## What's Safe-Submit?
<i>Safe-Submit</i> is a method in which a PvtPpr user can build a PvtPpr but not be presented with a viewable result. This uses a PvtPpr Branded Holding Hashlink that puroposly displays a bad page error but still places the full hashlink within the address bar. The link can be copied and opened in the <a href="https://3dd.in/PPFAQ" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">PvtPpr FAQ page</a>.

## PvtPpr Messages
PvtPpr Messages Generator is an extreamly light-weight PvtPpr Generator specifically designed to send the full hashlink to others as private messages. Instead of trusting the message company's database, sending the hashlink through the system doesn't directly store your words to their servers. Using short-links instead can allow you to send messages to someone through the same link everytime and at will, you can remove the link from the shortlink service (like rebrandly) to remove your messages from the messaging system's database.

## PvtPpr Internal Feartures
The main feature being presented in this generator is passing links through the itty.bitty.site's nodeJS encoder because it uses the selector and selects <code>&#60;a></code> for the inofrmation to be encoded.
  
  First we bring the make a new variable with an empty inside:
     <code>  var adstuff = ''; </code>
       
  Next we add into the new variable the code directly being inserted into the output location:     
    <code>   adstuff += '< a type="button" align="right;" href="' + document.getElementById('adlink').value + '" target="_blank"; ><span id="adtext" > < sup >< sub > ' + document.getElementById('adtextin').value + ' < / sub>< / sup>< / span>< / a><span id="adtxt" style="font-size:8px" ></br>  < b id="adtxtbottom" >ad< / b></ span>  '; </code>  
   
   In the input of the new variable inline styling may be used but more standard styling should work as well if the output styling is located within the selctor section. 
   
   Now we can apply the new filled variable to the output location:
    <code>   document.getElementById('adhere').innerHTML = adstuff;      </code>
       
       
   Repeating these we can pass images, videos, buttons and maybe more:    
 <code>      var topimg = '';     topimg += '< img src="' + document.getElementById('imglink').value + '" value="Image Link" />';     document.getElementById('img1').innerHTML = topimg;     </code>
 
 <i>A neat trick with the image pass, is if the input value is not a link but just text, the image transfer will become invalid and will not display a broken-link image nor a giant empty box in the output's location.</i>
       
   
The nodejs passing for ittybittysite is as follows:   
    <code>   a = document.querySelector('a'); LZMA.compress(a.outerHTML, 9, function(r) {a.innerText = a.href = 'https://itty.bitty.site/#/?' + btoa(String.fromCharCode.apply(null, new Uint8Array(r)))});}  </code>
